Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop them into a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil, season with
@salt and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Remove the @slow cooked British pork{425%g} from the packaging. Place in an
#ovenproof dish{} along with the juices and spread the @red Thai style paste{50%g} all over.

Cover loosely with #foil{} and roast on the middle shelf for
~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}. Reserve 2 leaves per person, then
thinly slice the rest widthways.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @rice vinegar{2%tbsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}. Stir together and season with @salt and @ground black pepper{}.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down
the length of the carrot, stopping at the core. Add the ribbons to the bowl
of dressing.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a
#rolling pin{}.

Once cooked, remove the pork from the oven, then discard the #foil{} and
any cooking juices.

Use two #forks{} to shred the pork as finely as you can. Return to the oven
uncovered for ~{5%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2} and pop them into the oven to warm
through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the pulled pork is ready, mix through the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} and
the @hoisin sauce{32%g}. Add a splash of @water if it's a little dry and
season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Toss the sliced baby gem and crushed peanuts with the carrot ribbons to make
your peanut salad.

When everything's ready, transfer the buns to your plates.

Load the bases with the pulled pork and top with the reserved baby gem leaves.

Serve the chips and peanut salad alongside.

Enjoy!